  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they were interned in a basement of a modern immigration hall.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was a modern building.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It was the same where I had arrived and saw all the paper, all my life was into the air.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And there they were interned for, I believe, two months, until the last one has-- has-- has had scarlet fever.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And then we board the ship, the to bring them from Cosenza to Israel.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And first of all, I had gone to Rhodes to get passengers in Rhodes in order to pay for the because the was there and was not used.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And Rhodes, I saved all the young people from Rhodes because those who did not go on the boat, then illegally were all deported.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "When the German got their orders from the Italians, or they took over.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They shipped the whole [INAUDIBLE] to Auschwitz, every single one of them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But we took a number of people, maybe 100 or 150 young people, from Rhodes who pay.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We had the ship, the monies to take again.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And to use the Was the trouble now, they loaded the people from Rhodes, and they was happy they left.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And they was on-- on the bus to the airport to fly back to Athens to continue to work for other ship from Vienna as they came on.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Always the desire of more more, more, we need more ships.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "We need more people.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And I had then the worst two hours of my life, on the-- still today, the worst two hours.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "On the bus-- the bus, it was-- I always thought there will be more trouble.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "There was never anything without more trouble, more trouble.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But I saw now on the bus, the people left, they are on their way and they're going to [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
